{{Infobox feature on celestial object |name = Annona |image = PIA20856-Ceres-DwarfPlanet-Dawn-4thMapOrbit-LAMO-image136-20160607.jpg |caption = Annona is on the top left of the photo |image_size = 300px |type = |location = [[Ceres (dwarf planet)|Ceres]] |coordinates= {{coord|48.14|S|8.43|E|globe:ceres_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |coordinates_footnotes = <ref name="GPN">{{cite web |title=Planetary Names: Crater, craters: Mondamin on Ceres |url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/15458 |date=14 December 2015 |publisher=Gazeteer of Planetary Nomenclature|work=[[USGS]] |accessdate=28 August 2017}}</ref> |length = |width = |diameter = {{convert|60|km|mi}} |depth = |area = |dimensions = |peak = |discoverer = |naming = |eponym = [[Annona (goddess)|Annona]], Roman goddess of crops and of the harvest }}
'''Annona''' <!--{{IPAc-en|}} -->is a small crater in the southern hemisphere of the dwarf planet [[Ceres (dwarf planet)|Ceres]], located at 48.14° S, 8.43° E. It has a diameter of {{convert|60|km|mi}}. The crater is named after [[Annona (goddess)|Annona]], a [[Roman mythology|Roman]] goddess of crops and of the harvest.<ref name="GPN"/> It was officially named by the [[International Astronomical Union|IAU]] on December 14, 2015.<ref name="GPN"/>
Nearby craters include the tiny [[Doliku (crater)|Doliku]] to the north, [[Sintana (crater)|Sintana]] further east, [[Zadeni (crater)|Zadeni]] to the southeast, [[Mondamin (crater)|Mondamin]] to the south and [[Tibong (crater)|Tibong]] and [[Belun (crater)|Belun]] to the north.
