{{Infobox organization | native_name = ''Drosos Stiftung'' | image = Drosos Foundation Logo.png | image_size = | alt = | caption = Logo for the Drosos Foundation | abbreviation = | motto = | formation = {{start date|2003|||df=y}} | founder = | type = [[NGO]] | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for non-profit org) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = [[Non-profit]] [[Charitable organization|Charity]] | purpose = | headquarters = [[Zurich]], [[Switzerland]] | coords = {{coord|47.3829|8.5424|display=inline,title}} | region = | services = | products = | methods = | fields = | membership = | membership_year = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = CEO | leader_name = Dr. Richard Brogle | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = {{plainlist| * '''Chairman:''' Lic. Markus E. Kronauer * '''Vice-Chairman:''' Dr. Frank Schnewlin * '''Members:''' {{plainlist| * Dr. Stefan Kraft * Lic. Edith Kreis-Kolb * Dr. Franz von Däniken }} }} | key_people = | affiliations = | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | staff = | staff_year = | volunteers = | volunteers_year = | mission = | website = {{url|drosos.org/en|drosos.org}} | remarks = | footnotes = }}
The '''Drosos Foundation''' ({{lang-de|Drosos Stiftung}}) is a [[non-profit]], [[Charitable organization|charitable]] organization based in [[Zurich]], [[Switzerland]]. Established in late 2003 with capital from a private endowment, the foundation was fully active by early 2005.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Christian Raaflaub|title=Outgoing diplomat praises bilateral route|url=http://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/outgoing-diplomat-praises-bilateral-route/4181468|publisher=[[swissinfo]]|accessdate=1 March 2015|date=4 November 2004}}</ref><ref name=swissinfo2011>{{cite web|author1=Abdelhafidh Abdeleli|title=More work for NGOs despite Arab spring clean|url=http://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/more-work-for-ngos-despite-arab-spring-clean/30438266|publisher=[[swissinfo]]|accessdate=1 March 2015|date=12 June 2011}}</ref> The foundation is involved with more than 100 projects as of 2015, which work to fight [[poverty]], promote health, increase access to education and creative activities for youth, and protect the environment.<ref name=swissinfo2011 /> The foundation also has offices in [[Cairo]], and [[Casablanca]].
