The following table is a '''list of [[postal code]]s in [[Croatia]]'''. Croatian postal codes have five digits, written without separator characters.
==Overview== [[File:2 digit postcode croatia.png|thumb|450px|2-digit postcode areas in Croatia (defined through the first two postcode digits)]] The first two digits correspond to each of the 20 [[counties of Croatia]] & [[City of Zagreb]], as follows:
* 1xxxx Zagreb region: ** 10xxx [[Zagreb|City of Zagreb]] and [[Zagreb County]]
* 2xxxx Southern Croatia: ** 20xxx [[Dubrovnik-Neretva County]] ** 21xxx [[Split-Dalmatia County]] ** 22xxx [[Šibenik-Knin County]] ** 23xxx [[Zadar County]]
* 3xxxx Eastern Croatia: ** 31xxx [[Osijek-Baranja County]] ** 32xxx [[Vukovar-Srijem County]] ** 33xxx [[Virovitica-Podravina County]] ** 34xxx [[Požega-Slavonia County]] ** 35xxx [[Brod-Posavina County]]
* 4xxxx Central Croatia except Zagreb region: ** 40xxx [[Međimurje County]] ** 42xxx [[Varaždin County]] ** 43xxx [[Bjelovar-Bilogora County]] ** 44xxx [[Sisak-Moslavina County]] ** 47xxx [[Karlovac County]] ** 48xxx [[Koprivnica-Križevci County]] ** 49xxx [[Krapina-Zagorje County]]
* 5xxxx Western Croatia: ** 51xxx [[Primorje-Gorski Kotar County]] ** 52xxx [[Istria County]] ** 53xxx [[Lika-Senj County]]
