{{Infobox website | name = OpenStreetCam | logo = Openstreetcam-logo.svg | url = {{URL|https://www.openstreetcam.org/}} | language = | content_license = CC-BY-SA | launch_date = 2009 | current_status = Active }}
'''OpenStreetCam''', formerly called '''OpenStreetView''', is a project to collect crowdsourced street-level photographs for improving [[OpenStreetMap]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/12/14/open_source_insider_openstreetview_takes_on_google/|title=OpenStreetView? You are no longer hostage to Google's car-driven vision|last=Gilbertson|first=Scott|date=14 December 2016|work=The Register|access-date=23 July 2017|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> operated by [[TeleNav]].<ref>https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2016/09/22/873840/0/en/Telenav-releases-OpenStreetView-an-automotive-integrated-open-source-platform-designed-to-accelerate-the-advancement-of-OpenStreetMap.html</ref> Collected imagery is published under a [[CC-BY-SA]] license and most of the project's code is [[Open-source software|open source]].<ref name=":0" />
Contributors gather imagery with their smartphones using an [[Android (operating system)|Android]] or [[iOS]] app.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.techworld.com/download/internet-tools/openstreetcam-147-ios-3330980/|title=OpenStreetCam 1.4.7 for iOS|last=Williams|first=Mike|date=24 December 2016|work=Techworld|access-date=23 July 2017|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> It is also possible to upload images captured with other cameras. The OpenStreetCam app supports using an [[On-board diagnostics|OBD-II]] dongle plugged into the vehicle; in concert with the mobile device's GPS, OSC can derive more accurate image locations. The app also recognizes and processes street signs in real time while capturing imagery.<ref name=":0" /> Once the imagery is recorded, it is uploaded, processed, and published to the website.<ref name=":1" />
OpenStreetMap editors can access OSC images using the [[iD (software)|iD]] editor or [[JOSM]] plugin.<ref name=":0" />
OpenStreetCam's purpose resembles that of [[Mapillary]]. The main difference between the two is that OpenStreetCam's web and mobile apps are open-source, whereas Mapillary is not. OpenStreetCam also makes it easier for user to delete their uploaded photos in case they change their mind about contributing.<ref name=":0" />
== History == OpenStreetCam was founded in 2009 as OpenStreetView.<ref name=":0" /> In 2016, TeleNav took over the openstreetview.org domain and started its own service under the name <ref>https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/OpenStreetCam</ref>. The service was renamed to OpenStreetCam after an intervention by an unnamed trademark holder.<ref>https://lists.openstreetmap.org/pipermail/talk/2016-November/077058.html</ref>
